  <h1>Cybersecurity Newsfeed</h1>
  <h2>📅 23/02/26</h2>

  <h2>🛡️ Vulnerabilities</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Mental health apps expose 14.7M users</strong>: Oversecured identified 1,575 vulnerabilities across ten popular Android mental health apps. Flaws include insecure URI parsing and hardcoded Firebase URLs, allowing attackers to intercept tokens and access sensitive therapy logs. Despite HIPAA relevance, many apps remain unpatched since late 2024. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/android-mental-health-apps-with-147m-installs-filled-with-security-flaws/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>16 Zero-days in Foxit and Apryse PDF platforms</strong>: Novee Security uncovered critical risks including OS command injection and SSRF (CVE-2025-70402/70401). Using an AI "swarm" for analysis, researchers found these platforms vulnerable to one-click account takeovers and remote code execution via malicious metadata. Patches have been released. <a href="https://hackread.com/zero-day-flaws-pdf-platforms-xss-one-click-attacks/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>🎯 Adversaries</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Spanish authorities dismantle "Anonymous Fénix"</strong>: The Civil Guard arrested four members of the hacktivist group responsible for DDoS attacks on government ministries. Active since 2023, the group ramped up activity following the 2024 Valencia floods. Their social media and communication infrastructure have been neutralized. <a href="https://www.bleepingcomputer.com/news/security/spain-arrests-suspected-anonymous-fenix-hacktivists-for-ddosing-govt-sites/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>APT28's Operation MacroMaze targets Europe</strong>: From late 2025 to early 2026, Russian state actors used spear-phishing with "INCLUDEPICTURE" beacons to track targets. The multi-stage chain uses Microsoft Edge in headless mode to render payloads, minimizing on-disk artifacts and bypassing traditional perimeters. <a href="https://thehackernews.com/2026/02/apt28-targeted-european-entities-using.html" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>MuddyWater deploys AI-assisted "Char" backdoor</strong>: Iran-linked actors launched "Operation Olalampo" targeting the Middle East and Africa. The campaign features the Rust-based Char backdoor, which shows signs of AI-assisted code generation. The group is also utilizing Telegram bots for C2 and AnyDesk for RMM. <a href="https://www.darkreading.com/threat-intelligence/iran-muddywater-new-malware-tensions-mount" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>Silver Fox impersonates Huorong Security</strong>: Targeting users in China, this APT group uses typosquatted domains to distribute ValleyRAT via the Winos4.0 framework. The infection utilizes DLL sideloading and modifies Windows Defender exclusions to ensure persistence for its modular plugins. <a href="https://www.malwarebytes.com/blog/scams/2026/02/huorong" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>📈 Trends</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Wormable XMRig campaign uses BYOVD</strong>: A cryptojacking campaign spreading via pirated software leverages a signed WinRing0x64.sys driver to boost mining efficiency. It features a "logic bomb" kill switch set for late 2025 to trigger a cleanup routine and evade long-term forensics. <a href="https://securityaffairs.com/188388/malware/wormable-xmrig-campaign-leverages-byovd-and-timed-kill-switch-for-stealth.html" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>"SANDWORM_MODE" supply chain worm hits npm</strong>: Socket identified a new worm targeting developer AI toolchains. It injects rogue Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers into assistants like Claude Desktop and Cursor, harvesting API keys and CI/CD secrets while establishing persistence via global git hooks. <a href="https://www.infosecurity-magazine.com/news/shai-hulud-like-worm-devs-npm-ai/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>ClawHub comments weaponized for AMOS infostealer</strong>: Threat actors are bypassing automated scans on the OpenClaw repository by hiding Base64-encoded payloads in comment sections. The malware targets macOS users, bypassing quarantine attributes to exfiltrate credentials and crypto wallets. <a href="https://www.helpnetsecurity.com/2026/02/23/clawhub-malicious-comment-infostealer/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>

    <li><strong>XWorm 7.2 delivered via steganographic JPEGs</strong>: A campaign exploiting CVE-2018-0802 uses malicious Excel attachments to trigger a fileless chain. It hides a .NET loader in JPEG images to perform process hollowing on Msbuild.exe, enabling data theft and DDoS capabilities. <a href="https://hackread.com/hackers-excel-exploit-xworm-7-2-jpeg-files-hijack-pcs/" target="_blank">More info</a></li>
  </ul>

  <h2>📚 Others</h2>
